obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (45576)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45576&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881.`
  line
  line `Local extent. Saving of usages relating to hundis, etc.--It extends to the whole of India ^1*** but`
  line `nothing herein contained affects the ^2Indian Paper Currency Act, 1871 (3 of 1871), section 21, or affects`
  line `any local usage relating to any instrument in an oriental language:`
  line
  line `Provided that such usages may be excluded by any words in the body of the instrument which`
  line `indicate an intention that the legal relations of the parties thereto shall he governed by this Act;`
  line
  line `Commencement.--and it shall come into force on the first day of March, 1882.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir", which were subs. by Act 3 of 1951, for "except Part B States", omitted`
  line `by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Sch.`
  line
  line `2. Rep. by the Indian Paper Currency Act, 1923 (10 of 1923). See now the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), s. 31.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (45577)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45577&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `[ Repeal of enactments.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1891 (12 of 1891), s. 2 and`
  line `the Schedule I.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (45578)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45578&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act--`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `Banker.^2[banker includes any person acting as a banker and any post office savings bank;]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Definition of the word India, which was subs. by Act 3 of 1951, for the definition of the word State, omitted by Act 62 of`
  line `1956, s. 2 and the Sch.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 37 of 1955, s. 2, for the definition of the word banker.`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by Act 53 of 1952, s. 16 (w.e.f. 14-2-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (45579)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `''Promissory note''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45579&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A "Promissory note" is an instrument in writing (not being a bank-note or a`
  line `currency-note) containing an unconditional undertaking, signed by the maker, to pay a certain sum of`
  line `money only to, or to the order of, a certain person, or to the bearer of the instrument.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `A signs instruments in the following terms:`
  line
  line `(a ) "I promise to pay B or order Rs. 500."`
  line
  line `(b) "I acknowledge myself to be indebted to B in Rs. 1,000, to be paid on demand, for value received."`
  line
  line `(c) "Mr. B, I O U Rs. 1,000.`
  line
  line `(d) "I promise to Pay B Rs. 500 and all other sums which shall be due to him."`
  line
  line `(e) "I promise to Pay B Rs. 500, first deducting thereout any money which he may owe me."`
  line
  line `(f) "I promise to Pay B Rs. 500 seven days after my marriage with C."`
  line
  line `(g) "I, promise to Pay B Rs. 500 on D's death, provided D leaves me enough to pay that sum."`
  line
  line `(h) "I promise to Pay B Rs. 500 and to deliver to him my black horse on 1st January next."`
  line
  line `The instruments respectively marked (a) and (b) are promissory notes. The instruments respectively marked (c),`
  line `(d), (e), (f), (g) and (h) are not promissory notes.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (45580)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `''Bill of exchange''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45580&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A "bill of exchange" is an instrument in writing containing an unconditional`
  line `order, signed by the maker, directing a certain person to pay a certain sum of money only to, or to the`
  line `order of, a certain person or to the bearer of the instrument.`
  line
  line `A promise or order to pay is not "conditional", within the meaning of this section and section 4, by`
  line `reason of the time for payment of the amount or any instalment thereof being expressed to be on the lapse`
  line `of a certain period after the occurrence of a specified event which, according to the ordinary expectation of`
  line `mankind, is certain to happen, although the time of its happening may be uncertain.`
  line
  line `The sum payble may be "certain", within the meaning of this section and section 4, although it`
  line `includes future interest or is payable at an indicated rate of exchange, or is according to the course of`
  line `exchange, and although the instrument provides that, on default of payment of an instalment, the balance`
  line `unpaid shall become due.`
  line
  line `The person to whom it is clear that the direction is given or that payment is to be made may be a`
  line `"certain person", within the meaning of this section and section 4, although he is mis-named or`
  line `designated by description only.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (45581)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `''Cheque''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45581&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[A cheque is a bill of exchange drawn on a specified banker and not expressed to`
  line `be payable otherwise than on demand and it includes the electronic image of a truncated cheque and a`
  line `cheque in the electronic form.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.-- For the purposes of this section, the expressions`
  line
  line `^2[(a) a cheque in the electronic form means a cheque drawn in electronic form by using any`
  line `computer resource and signed in a secure system with digital signature (with or without biometrics`
  line `signature) and asymmetric crypto system or with electronic signature, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `(b) a truncated cheque means a cheque which is truncated during the course of a clearing cycle,`
  line `either by the clearing house or by the bank whether paying or receiving payment, immediately on`
  line `generation of an electronic image for transmission, substituting the further physical movement of the`
  line `cheque in writing.`
  line
  line `Explanation II. -- For the purposes of this section, the expression clearing house means the clearing`
  line `house managed by the Reserve Bank of India or a clearing house recognised as such by the Reserve Bank`
  line `of India.]`
  line
  line `^3[Explanation III. -- For the purposes of this section, the expressions asymmetric crypto system,`
  line `computer resource, digital signature, electronic form and electronic signature shall have the same`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000).]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 2002, s. 2, for s. 6 (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 2015, s. 2, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 15-6-2015)`
  line
  line `3. The Explanation III, ins. by s. 2, ibid, (w.e.f. 15-6-2015)`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (45730)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `''Drawer.''`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1885, s. 2, for When acceptance is refused and the bill is protested for non -acceptance.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45730&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The maker of a bill of exchange or cheque is called the drawer; the`
  line `person thereby directed to pay is called the drawee.`
  line
  line `"Drawee in case of need". -- When in the Bill or in any indorsement thereon the name of any person`
  line `is given in addition to the drawee to be resorted to in case of need such person is called a "drawee in case`
  line `of need".`
  line
  line `"Acceptor". -- After the drawee of a bill has signed his assent upon the bill, or, if there are more parts`
  line `thereof than one, upon one of such parts, and delivered the same, or given notice of such signing to the`
  line `holder or to some person on his behalf, he is called the "acceptor".`
  line
  line `"Acceptor for honour". -- ^1[When a bill of exchange has been noted or protested for non-acceptance or for better security,] and any person accepts it supra protest for honour of the drawer or of`
  line `any one of the indorsers, such person is called an "acceptor for honour".`
  line
  line `"Payee". -- The person named in the instrument, to whom or to whose order the money is by the`
  line `instrument directed to be paid, is called the "payee".`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (45583)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `''Holder''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45583&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The "holder" of a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque means any person`
  line `entitled in his own name to the possession thereof and to receive or recover the amount due thereon from`
  line `the parties thereto.`
  line
  line `Where the note, bill or cheque is lost or destroyed, its holder is the person so entitled at the time of`
  line `such loss or destruction.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (45584)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `''Holder in due course''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 1919. s. 2, for "payable to, or to the order of, a payee", .`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45584&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `"Holder in due course" means any person who for consideration`
  line `became the possessor of a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque if payable to bearer,`
  line
  line `or the payee or indorsee thereof, if ^1[payable to order,]`
  line
  line `before the amount mentioned in it became payable, and without having sufficient cause to believe that`
  line `any defect existed in the title of the person from whom he derived his title.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (45585)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `''Payment in due course''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45585&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `"Payment in due course" means payment in accordance with the`
  line `apparent tenor of the instrument in good faith and without negligence to any person in possession thereof`
  line `under circumstances which do not afford a reasonable ground for believing that he is not entitled to`
  line `receive payment of the amount therein mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (45586)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Inland instrument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1957, s. 3 and the Second Schedule "a State".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45586&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `A promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque drawn or made in ^1[India]`
  line `and made payable in, or drawn upon any person resident in, ^1[India] shall be deemed to be an inland`
  line instrument.
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (45587)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Foreign instrument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45587&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Any such instrument not so drawn, made or made payable shall be`
  line `deemed to be a foreign instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (45588)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `''Negotiable instrument''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45588&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) A negotiable instrument means a promissory note, bill of`
  line `exchange or cheque payable either to order or to bearer.`
  line
  line `Explanation (i) -- A promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque is payable to order which is`
  line `expressed to be so payable or which is expressed to be payable to a particular person, and does not`
  line `contain words prohibiting transfer or indicating an intention that it shall not be transferable.`
  line
  line `Explanation (ii) -- A promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque is payble to bearer which is`
  line `expressed to be so payable or on which the only or last indorsement is an indorsement in blank.`
  line
  line `Explanation (iii) -- Where a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque, either originally or by`
  line `indorsement, is expressed to be payable to the order of a specified person, and not to him or his`
  line `order, it is nevertheless payable to him or his order at his option.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) A negotiable instrument may be made payable to two or more payees jointly, or it may be made`
  line `payable in the alternative to one of two, or one or some of serveral payees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 1919, s. 3, for the original sub-section.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 5 of 1914, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (45589)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Negotiation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45589&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `When a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque is transferred to any person,`
  line `so as to constitute that person the holder thereof, the instrument is said to be negotiated.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (45590)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Indorsement.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45590&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `When the maker or holder of a negotiable instrument signs the same, otherwise`
  line `than as such maker, for the purpose of negotiation, on the back or face thereof or on a slip of paper`
  line `annexed thereto, or so signs for the same purpose a stamped paper intended to be completed as a`
  line `negotiable instrument, he is said to indorse the same, and is called the "indorser".`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (45591)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Indorsement ''in blank'' and ''in full''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45591&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] If the indorser signs his name only, the`
  line `indorsement is said to be "in blank," and if he adds a direction to pay the amount mentioned in the`
  line `instrument to, or to the order of, a specified person, the indorsement is said to be "in full", and the`
  line `person so specified`
  line
  line `"Indorsee".--is called the “indorsee” of the instrument.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The provisions of this Act relating to a payee shall apply with the necessary modifications to an`
  line indorsee.]
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 16 renumbered as sub-section (1) by s. 3, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 5 of 1914, s. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (45592)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Ambiguous instruments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45592&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Where an instrument may be construed either as a promissory note or`
  line `bill of exchange, the holder may at his election treat it as either, and the instrument shall be thenceforward`
  line `treated accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (45593)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Where amount is stated differently in figures and words.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45593&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `If the amount undertaken or`
  line `ordered to be paid is stated differently in figures and in words, the amount stated in words shall be the`
  line `amount undertaken or ordered to be paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (45594)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Instruments payable on demand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45594&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `A promissory note or bill of exchange, in which no time for`
  line `payment is specified, and a cheque, are payable on demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (45595)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Inchoate stamped instruments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch., for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45595&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where one person signs and delivers to another a paper`
  line `stamped in accordance with the law relating to negotiable instruments then in force in ^1[India], and`
  line `either wholly blank or having written thereon an incomplete negotiable instrument, he thereby gives`
  line `prima facie authority to the holder thereof to make or complete, as the case may be, upon it a`
  line `negotiable instrument, for any amount specified therein and not exceeding the amount covered by the`
  line `stamp. The person so signing shall be liable upon such instrument, in the capacity in which he signed`
  line `the same, to any holder in due course for such amount: provided that no person other than a holder in`
  line `due course shall recover from the person delivering the instrument anything in excess of the amount`
  line `intended by him to be paid thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (45596)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `''At sight''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45596&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `In a promissory note or bill of exchange the expressions "at`
  line `sight" and "on presentment" mean on demand. The expression "After sight"--"after sight" means, in a`
  line `promissory note, after presentment for sight, and, in a bill of exchange, after acceptance, or nothing for`
  line `non-acceptance, or protest for non-acceptance.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (45597)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `''Maturity''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45597&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The maturity of a promissory note or bill of exchange is the date at which it falls`
  line due.
  line
  line `Days of grace.--Every promissory note or bill of exchange which is not expressed to be payable on`
  line `demand, at sight or on presentment is at maturity on the third day after the day on which it is expressed to`
  line `be payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (45598)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Calculating maturity of bill or note payable so many months after date or sight.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45598&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line In
  line `calculating the date at which a promissary note or bill of exchange, made payable a stated number of`
  line `months after date or after sight, or after a certain event, is at maturity, the period stated shall be held to`
  line `terminate on the day of the month which corresponds with the day on which the instrument is dated, or`
  line `presented for acceptance or sight, or noted for non-acceptance, or protested for non-acceptance, or the`
  line `event happens, or, where the instrument is a bill of exchange made payable a stated number of months after`
  line `sight and has been accepted for honour, with the day on which it was so accepted. If the month in which`
  line `the period would terminate has no corresponding day, the period shall be held to terminate on the last`
  line `day of such month.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A negotiable instrument, dated 29th January, 1878, is made payable at one month after date. The instrument is at`
  line `maturity on the third day after the 28th February, 1878.`
  line
  line `(b) A negotiable instrument, dated 30th August, 1878, is made payable three months after date. The instrument is at`
  line `maturity on the 3rd December, 1878.`
  line
  line `(c) A promissory note or bill of exchange, dated 31st August, 1878, is made payable three months after date. The`
  line `instrument is at maturity on the 3rd December, 1878.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (45599)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Calculating maturity of bill or note payable so many days after date or sight.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45599&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `In calculating`
  line `the date at which a promissory note or bill of exchange made payable a certain number of days after date`
  line `or after sight or after a certain event is at maturity, the day of the date, or of presentment for acceptance or`
  line `sight, or of protest for non-acceptance, or on which the event happens, shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (45600)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `When day of maturity is a holiday.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45600&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `When the day on which a promissory note or bill of`
  line `exchange is at maturity is a public holiday, the instrument shall be deemed to be due on the next`
  line `preceding, business day.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- The expression "public holiday" includes Sundays: ^1*** and any other day declared`
  line `by the ^2[Central Government], by notification in the Official Gazette, to be a public holiday.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words New Year's day, Christmas day: if either of such days falls on a Sunday, the next following Monday: GoodFriday: omitted by Act 37 of 1955, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs by the A.O. 1937, for L.G.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (45601)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Capacity to make, etc., promissory notes, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45601&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every person capable of contracting, according`
  line `to the law to which he is subject, may bind himself and be bound by the making, drawing, acceptance,`
  line `indorsement, delivery and negotiation of a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque.`
  line
  line `Minor.--A minor may draw, indorse, deliver and negotiate such instrument so as to bind all parties`
  line `except himself.`
  line
  line `Nothing herein contained shall be deemed to empower a corporation to make, indorse or accept such`
  line `instruments except in cases in which, under the law for the time being in force, they are so empowered.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (45602)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title Agency.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45602&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Every person capable of binding himself or of being bound, as mentioned in section`
  line `26, may so bind himself or be bound by a duly authorized agent acting in his name.`
  line
  line `A general authority to transact business and to receive and discharge debts does not confer upon an`
  line `agent the power of accepting or indorsing bills of exchange so as to bind his principal.`
  line
  line `An authority to draw bills of exchange does not of itself import an authority to indorse.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (45603)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Liability of agent signing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45603&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `An agent who signs his name to a promissory note, bill of exchange`
  line `or cheque without indicating thereon that he signs as agent, or that he does not intend thereby to incur`
  line `personal responsibility, is liable personally on the instrument, except to those who induced him to sign`
  line `upon the belief that the principal only would be held liable.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (45604)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Liability of legal representative signing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45604&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `A legal representative of a deceased person who`
  line `signs his name to a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque is liable personally thereon unless he`
  line `expressly limits his liability to the extent of the assets received by him as such.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (45605)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Liability of drawer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45605&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The drawer of a bill of exchange or cheque is bound, in case of dishonour`
  line `by the drawee or acceptor thereof, to compensate the holder, provided due notice of dishonour has been`
  line `given to, or received by, the drawer as hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (45606)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Liability of drawee of cheque.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45606&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The drawee of a cheque having sufficient funds of the drawer in his`
  line `hands properly applicable to the payment of such cheque must pay the cheque when duly required so to do,`
  line `and , in default of such payment, must compensate the drawer for any loss or damage caused by such default.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (45607)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Liability of maker of note and acceptor of bill.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45607&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of a contract to the contrary, the`
  line `maker of a promissory note and the acceptor before maturity of a bill of exchange are bound to pay the`
  line `amount thereof at maturity according to the apparent tenor of the note or acceptance respectively, and the`
  line `acceptor of a bill of exchange at or after maturity is bound to pay the amount thereof to the holder on demand.`
  line
  line `In default of such payment as aforesaid, such maker or acceptor is bound to compensate any party to`
  line `the note or bill for any loss or damage sustained by him and caused by such default.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (45608)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Only drawee can be acceptor except in need or for honour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45608&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No person except the drawee of`
  line `a bill exchange, or all or some of several drawees, or a person named therein as a drawee in case of need,`
  line `or an acceptor for honour, can bind himself by an acceptance.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (45609)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Acceptance by several drawees not partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45609&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Where there are several drawees of a bill of`
  line `exchange who are not partners, each of them can accept it for himself, but none of them can accept it for`
  line `another without his authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (45610)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Liability of indorser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45610&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of a contract to the contrary, whoever indorses and delivers a`
  line `negotiable instrument before maturity without, in such it indorsement, expressly excluding or making`
  line `conditional his own liability, is bound thereby to every subsequent holder, in case of dishonour by the`
  line `drawee, acceptor or maker, to compensate such holder for any loss or damage caused to him by such`
  line `dishonour, provided due notice of dishonour has been given to, or received by, such indorser as hereinafter`
  line provided.
  line
  line `Every indorser after dishonour is liable as upon an instrument payable on demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (45611)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Liability of prior parties to holder in due course.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45611&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Every prior party to a negotiable instrument`
  line `is liable thereon to a holder in due course until the instrument is duly satisfied.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (45612)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Maker, drawer and acceptor principals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45612&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The maker of a promissory note or cheque, the drawer of`
  line `a bill of exchange until acceptance, and the acceptor are, in the absence of a contract to the contrary,`
  line `respectively liable thereon as principal debtors, and the other parties thereto are liable thereon as sureties for`
  line `the maker, drawer or acceptor, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (45613)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Prior party a principal in respect of each subsequent party.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45613&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `As between the parties so liable`
  line `as sureties, each prior party is, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, also liable thereon as a`
  line `principal debtor in respect of each subsequent party.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A draws a bill payable to his own order on B, who accepts. A afterwards indorses the bill to C, C to D, and D to E. As`
  line `between E and B, B is the principal debtor, and A, C and D are his sureties. As between E and A, A is the principal debtor, and C`
  line `and D are his sureties. As between E and C, C is the principal debtor and D is his surety.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (45614)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title Suretyship.
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45614&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `When the holder of an accepted bill of exchange enters into any contract with the`
  line `acceptor which, under section 134 or 135 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), would discharge`
  line `the other parties, the holder may expressly reserve his right to charge the other parties, and in such case`
  line `they are not discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (45615)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Discharge of indorser's liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45615&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Where the holder of a negotiable instrument, without the`
  line `consent of the indorser, destroys or impairs the indorser's remedy against a prior party, the indorser is`
  line `discharged from liability to the holder to the same extent as if the instrument had been paid at maturity.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A is the holder of a bill of exchange made payable to the order of B, which contains the following indorsements in`
  line `blank:--`
  line
  line `First indorsement, "B".`
  line
  line `Second indorsement, "Peter Williams".`
  line
  line `Third indorsement, "Wright & Co".`
  line
  line `Fourth indorsement. "John Rozario".`
  line
  line `This bill A puts in suit against John Rozario and strikes out, without John Rozario's consent, the indorsements by Peter`
  line `Williams and Wright & Co. A is not entitled to recover anything from John Rozario.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (45616)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Acceptor bound, although, indorsement forged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45616&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `An acceptor of a bill of exchange already`
  line `indorsed is not relieved from liability by reason that such indorsement is forged, if he knew or had reason`
  line `to believe the indorsement to be forged when he accepted the bill.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (45617)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Acceptance of bill drawn in fictitious name.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45617&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `An acceptor of a bill of exchange drawn in a`
  line `fictitious name and payable to the drawer's order is not, by reason that such name is fictitious, relieved`
  line `from liability to any holder in due course claiming under an indorsement by the same hand as the drawer's`
  line `signature, and purporting to be made by the drawer.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (45618)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Negotiable instrument made, etc., without consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45618&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `A negotiable instrument made,`
  line `drawn, accepted, indorsed or transferred without consideration, or for a consideration which fails, creates`
  line `no obligation of payment between the parties to the transaction. But if any such party has transferred the`
  line `instrument with or without indorsement to a holder for consideration, such holder, and every subsequent`
  line `holder deriving title from him, may recover the amount due on such instrument from the transferor for`
  line `consideration or any prior party thereto.`
  line
  line `Exception I.-- No party for whose accommodation a negotiable instrument has been made, drawn,`
  line `accepted or indorsed can, if he have paid the amount thereof, recover thereon such amount from any`
  line `person who became a party to such instrument for his accommodation.`
  line
  line `Exception II.-- No party to the instrument who has induced any other party to make, draw, accept, indorse`
  line `or transfer the same to him for a consideration which he has failed to pay or perform in full shall recover`
  line `thereon an amount exceeding the value of the consideration (if any) which he has actually paid or performed.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (45619)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Partial absence or failure of money-consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45619&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `When the consideration for which a`
  line `person signed a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque consisted of money, and was originally`
  line `absent in part or has subsequently failed in part, the sum which a holder standing in immediate relation`
  line `with such signer is entitled to receive from him is proportionally reduced.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- The drawer of a bill of exchange stands in immediate relation with the acceptor. The`
  line `maker of a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque stands in immediate relation with the payee, and`
  line `the indorser with his indorsee. Other signers may by agreement stand in immediate relation with a holder.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A draws a bill on B for Rs. 500 payable to the order of A, B accepts the bill, but subsequently dishonours, it by`
  line `non-payment. A sues B on the bill, B proves that it was accepted for value as to Rs. 400, and as an accommodation to`
  line `the plaintiff as to the residue. A can only recover Rs. 400.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (45620)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Partial failure of consideration not consisting of money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45620&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Where a part of the consideration`
  line `for which a person signed a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque, though not consisting of money,`
  line `is ascertainable in money without collateral enquiry, and there has been a failure of that part, the sum`
  line `which a holder standing in immediate relation with such signer is entitled to receive from him is`
  line `proportionally reduced.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45_a:
  sectionId (45621)
  sectionNo 45A
  orderNo 46
  title `Holder's right to duplicate of lost bill.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1885, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45621&sectionno=45A&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_45_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[Where a bill of exchange has been lost before it is`
  line `over-due, the person who was the holder of it may apply to the drawer to give him another bill of the`
  line `same tenor, giving security to the drawer, if required, to indemnify him against all persons whatever in`
  line `case the bill alleged to have been lost shall be found again.`
  line
  line `If the drawer on request as aforesaid refuses to give such duplicate bill, he may be compelled to do`
  line so.]
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (45622)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 47
  title Delivery.
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45622&sectionno=46&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The making, acceptance or indorsement of a promissory note, bill of exchange or`
  line `cheque is completed by delivery, actual or constructive.`
  line
  line `As between parties standing in immediate relation, delivery to be effectual must be made by the party`
  line `making, accepting or indorsing the instrument, or by a person authorised by him in that behalf.`
  line
  line `As between such parties and any holder of the instrument other than a holder in due course, it may be`
  line `shown that the instrument was delivered conditionally or for a special purpose only, and not for the`
  line `purpose of transferring absolutely the property therein.`
  line
  line `A promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque payable to bearer is negotiable by the delivery thereof.`
  line
  line `A promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque payable to order is negotiable by the holder by`
  line `indorsement and delivery thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (45623)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 48
  title `Negotiation by delivery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45623&sectionno=47&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 58, a promissory note, bill of`
  line `exchange or cheque payable to bearer is negotiable by delivery thereof.`
  line
  line `Exception.-- A promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque delivered on condition that it is not to`
  line `take effect except in a certain event is not negotiable (except in the hands of a holder for value without`
  line `notice of the condition) unless such event happens.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, the holder of a negotiable instrument payable to bearer, delivers it to B's agent to keep for B. The instrument has been`
  line negotiated.
  line
  line `(b) A, the holder of a negotiable instrument payable to bearer, which is in the hands of A's banker, who is at the time the`
  line `banker of B, directs the banker to transfer the instrument to B's credit in the banker's account with B. The banker does so, and`
  line `accordingly now possesses the instrument as B's agent. The instrument has been negotiated, and B has become the holder of it.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (45624)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 49
  title `Negotiation by indorsement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 1919, s. 4, for payable to the order of a specified person, or to a specified person or order.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45624&sectionno=48&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 58, a promissory note, bill of`
  line `exchange or cheque ^1[payable to order], is negotiable by the holder by indorsement and delivery thereof`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (45625)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 50
  title `Conversion of indorsement in blank into indorsement in full.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45625&sectionno=49&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The holder of a negotiable`
  line `instrument indorsed in blank may, without signing his own name, by writing above the indorser's`
  line `signature a direction to pay to any other person as indorsee, convert the indorsement in blank into an`
  line `indorsement in full; and the holder does not thereby incur the responsibility of an indorser.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (45626)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 51
  title `Effect of indorsement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45626&sectionno=50&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The indorsement of a negotiable instrument followed by delivery`
  line `transfers to the indorsee the property therein with the right of further negotiation; but the indorsement`
  line `may, by express words, restrict or exclude such right, or may merely constitute the indorsee an agent to`
  line `indorse the instrument, or to receive its contents for the indorser, or for some other specified person.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `B signs the following indorsements on different negotiable instruments payable to bearer.--`
  line
  line `(a) "Pay the contents to C only".`
  line
  line `(b) "Pay C for my use."`
  line
  line `(c) "Pay C or order for the account of B."`
  line
  line `(d) "the within must be credited to C."`
  line
  line `These indorsements exclude the right of further negotiation by C.`
  line
  line `(e) "Pay C."`
  line
  line `(f) "Pay C value in account with the Oriental Bank."`
  line
  line `(g) "Pay the contents to C, being part of the consideration in a certain deed of assignment executed by C to the indorser`
  line `and others."`
  line
  line `These indorsements do not exclude the right of further negotiation by C.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (45627)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 52
  title `Who may negotiate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45627&sectionno=51&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Every sole maker, drawer, payee or indorsee, or all of several joint`
  line `makers, drawers, payees or indorsees, of a negotiable instrument may, if the negotiability of such`
  line `instrument has not been restricted or excluded as mentioned in section 50, indorse and negotiate the same.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- Nothing in this section enables a maker or drawer to indorse or negotiate an`
  line `instrument, unless he is in lawful possession or is holder thereof; or enables a payee or indorsee to indorse`
  line `or negotiate an instrument, unless he is holder thereof.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A bill is drawn payable to A or order. A indorses it to B, the indorsement not containing the words "or order" or any`
  line `equivalent words. B may negotiate the instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (45628)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 53
  title `Indorser who excludes his own liability or makes it conditional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45628&sectionno=52&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The indorser of a negotiable`
  line `instrument may, by express words in the indorsement, exclude his own liability thereon, or make such liability or the right of the indorsee to receive the amount due thereon depend upon the happening of a`
  line `specified event, although such event may never happen.`
  line
  line `Where an indorser so excludes his liability and afterwards becomes the holder of the instrument, all`
  line `intermediate indorsers are liable to him.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) The indorser of a negotiable instrument sign; his name adding the words-- "Without recourse".`
  line
  line `Upon this indorsement he incurs no liability.`
  line
  line `(b) A is the payee and holder of a negotiable instrument. Excluding personal liability by an indorsement`
  line `"without recourse" he transfers the instrument to B, and B indorses it to C, who indorses it to A. A is not only`
  line `reinstated in his former rights, but has the rights of an indorsee against B and C.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (45629)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 54
  title `Holder deriving title from holder in due course.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45629&sectionno=53&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `A holder of a negotiable instrument who`
  line `derives title from a holder in due course has the rights thereon of that holder in due course.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (45630)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 55
  title `Instrument indorsed in blank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45630&sectionno=54&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions hereinafter contained as to crossed`
  line `cheques, a negotiable instrument indorsed in blank is payable to the bearer thereof even although`
  line `originally payable to order.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (45631)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 56
  title `Conversion of indorsement in blank into indorsement in full.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45631&sectionno=55&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `If a negotiable instrument,`
  line `after having been indorsed in blank, is indorsed in full, the amount of it cannot be claimed from the`
  line `indorser in full, except by the person to whom it has been indorsed in full, or by one who derives title`
  line `through such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (45632)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 57
  title `Indorsement for part of sum due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45632&sectionno=56&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `No writing on a negotiable instrument is valid for the`
  line `purpose of`
  line `negotiation if such writing purports to transfer only a part of the amount appearing to be due on the`
  line `instrument; but where such amount has been partly paid, a note to that effect may be indorsed on the`
  line `instrument, which may then be negotiated for the balance.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (45633)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 58
  title `Legal representative cannot by delivery only negotiate instrument indorsed by deceased.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45633&sectionno=57&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `The legal representative of a deceased person cannot negotiate by delivery only a promissory note, bill of`
  line `exchange or cheque payable to order and indorsed by the deceased but not delivered.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (45634)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 59
  title `Instrument obtained by unlawful means or for unlawful consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45634&sectionno=58&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `When a negotiable`
  line `instrument has been lost, or has been obtained from any maker, acceptor or holder thereof by means of an`
  line `offence or fraud, or for an unlawful consideration, no possessor or indorsee who claims through the`
  line `person who found or so obtained the instrument is entitled to receive the amount due thereon from such`
  line `maker, acceptor or holder, or from any party prior to such holder, unless such possessor or indorsee is, or`
  line `some person through whom he claims was, a holder thereof in due course.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (45635)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 60
  title `Instrument acquired after dishonour or when overdue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45635&sectionno=59&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The holder of a negotiable`
  line `instrument, who has acquired it after dishonour, whether by non-acceptance or non-payment, with notice`
  line `thereof, or after maturity, has only, as against the other parties, the rights thereon of his transferor:`
  line
  line `Accommodation note or bill.-- Provided that any person who, in good faith and for consideration,`
  line `becomes the holder, after maturity, of a promissory note or bill of exchange made, drawn or accepted`
  line `without consideration, for the purpose of enabling some party thereto to raise money thereon, may`
  line `recover the amount of the note or bill from any prior party.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `The acceptor of a bill of exchange, when he accepted it, deposited with the drawer certain goods as a collateral security for`
  line `the payment of the bill, with power to the drawer to sell the goods and apply the proceeds in discharge of the bill if it were not`
  line `paid at maturity. The bill not having been paid at maturity, the drawer sold the goods and retained the proceeds, but indorsed the`
  line `bill to A. A's title is subject to the same objection as the drawer's title.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (45636)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 61
  title `Instrument negotiable till payment or satisfaction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45636&sectionno=60&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `A negotiable instrument may be`
  line `negotiated (except by the maker, drawee or acceptor after maturity) until payment or satisfaction thereof`
  line `by the maker, drawee or acceptor at or after maturity, but not after such payment or satisfaction.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (45637)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 62
  title `Presentment for acceptance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1.Ins. by Act 2 of 1885, s. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45637&sectionno=61&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `A bill of exchange payable after sight must, if no time or place is`
  line `specified therein for presentment, be presented to the drawee thereof for acceptance, if he can, after`
  line `reasonable search, be found, by a person entitled to demand acceptance, within a reasonable time after it`
  line `is drawn, and in business hours on a business day. In default of such presentment, no party thereto is`
  line `liable thereon to the person making such default.`
  line
  line `If the drawee cannot, after reasonable search, be found, the bill is dishonoured.`
  line
  line `If the bill is directed to the drawee at a particular place, it must be presented at that place; and if at the`
  line `due date for presentment he cannot, after reasonable search, be found there, the till is dishonoured.`
  line
  line `^1[Where authorized by agreement or usage, a presentment through the post office by means of a registered`
  line `letter is sufficient.]`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (45638)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 63
  title `Presentment of promissory note for sight.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45638&sectionno=62&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `A promissory note, payable at a certain period after`
  line `sight, must be presented to the maker thereof for sight (if he can after reasonable search be found) by a person`
  line `entitled to demand payment, within a reasonable time after it is made and in business hours on a business day.`
  line `In default of such presentment, no party thereto is liable thereon to the person making such default.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (45639)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 64
  title `Drawee's time for deliberation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1921, s. 2, for "twenty-four".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45639&sectionno=63&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `The holder must, if so required by the drawee of a bill of`
  line `exchange presented to him for acceptance, allow the drawee ^1[forty-eight] hours (exclusive of public holidays) to consider whether he will accept it.`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (45640)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 65
  title `Presentment for payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45640&sectionno=64&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `^2[(1)] Promissory notes, bills of exchange and cheques must be`
  line `presented for payment to the maker, acceptor or drawee thereof respectively, by or on behalf of the holder`
  line `as hereinafter provided. In default of such presentment, the other parties thereto are not liable thereon to`
  line `such holder.`
  line
  line `^1[Where authorized by agreement or usage, a presentment through the post office by means of a`
  line `registered letter is sufficient.]`
  line
  line `Exception.--Where a promissory note is payable on demand and is not payable at a specified place,`
  line `no presentment is necessary in order to charge the maker thereof.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 6, where an electronic image of a truncated`
  line `cheque is presented for payment, the drawee bank is entitled to demand any further information regarding`
  line `the truncated cheque from the bank holding the truncated cheque in case of any reasonable suspicion`
  line `about the genuineness of the apparent tenor of instrument, and if the suspicion is that of any fraud,`
  line `forgery, tampering or destruction of the instrument, it is entitled to further demand the presentment of the`
  line `truncated cheque itself for verification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the truncated cheque so demanded by the drawee bank shall be retained by it, if the`
  line `payment is made accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Added by Act 2 of 1885, s. 4.`
  line
  line `2. Section 64 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 55 of 2002, s. 3 (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 3, ibid, (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (45641)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 66
  title `Hours for presentment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45641&sectionno=65&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Presentment for payment must be made during the usual hours of`
  line `business and, if at a banker's within banking hours.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (45642)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 67
  title `Presentment for payment of instrument payable after date or sight.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45642&sectionno=66&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `A promissory note or`
  line `bill of exchange, made payable at a specified period after date or sight thereof, must be presented for`
  line `payment at maturity.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (45643)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 68
  title `Presentment for payment of promissory note payable by instalments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45643&sectionno=67&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `A promissory note`
  line `payable by instalments must be presented for payment on the third day after the date fixed for payment of`
  line `each instalment; and non-payment on such presentment has the same effect as non-payment of a note at`
  line maturity.
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (45644)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 69
  title `Presentment for payment of instrument payable at specified place and not elsewhere.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45644&sectionno=68&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line A
  line `promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque made, drawn or accepted payable at a specified place and not`
  line `elsewhere must, in order to charge any party thereto, be presented for payment at that place.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (45645)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 70
  title `Instrument payable at specified place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45645&sectionno=69&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `A promissory note or bill of exchange made, drawn or`
  line `accepted payable at a specified place must, in order to charge the maker or drawer thereof, be presented`
  line `for payment at that place.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (45646)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 71
  title `Presentment where no exclusive place specified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45646&sectionno=70&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `A promissory note or bill of exchange, not`
  line `made payable as mentioned in sections 68 and 69, must be presented for payment at the place of business`
  line `(if any), or at the usual residence, of the maker, drawee or acceptor thereof, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (45647)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 72
  title `Presentment when maker, etc., has no known place of business or residence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45647&sectionno=71&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `If the maker,`
  line `drawee or acceptor of a negotiable instrument has no known place of business or fixed residence, and no`
  line `place is specified in the instrument for presentment for acceptance or payment such presentment may be`
  line `made to him in person wherever he can be found.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (45648)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 73
  title `Presentment of cheque to charge drawer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1897, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45648&sectionno=72&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `^1[Subject to the provisions of section 84,] a cheque`
  line `must, in order to charge the drawer, be presented at the bank upon which it is drawn before the relation`
  line `between the drawer and his banker has been altered to the prejudice of the drawer.`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (45649)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 74
  title `Presentment of cheque to charge any other person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45649&sectionno=73&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `A cheque must, in order to charge any`
  line `person except the drawer, be presented within a reasonable time after delivery thereof by such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (45650)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 75
  title `Presentment of instrument payable on demand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45650&sectionno=74&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 31, a`
  line `negotiable instrument payable on demand must be presented for payment within a reasonable time after it`
  line `is received by the holder.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (45651)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 76
  title `Presentment by or to agent, representative of deceased, or assignee of insolvent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45651&sectionno=75&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Presentment for acceptance or payment may be made to the duly authorized agent of the drawee, maker`
  line `or acceptor, as the case may be, or, where the drawee, maker or acceptor has died, to his legal`
  line `representative, or, where he has been declared an insolvent, to his assignee.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75_a:
  sectionId (45652)
  sectionNo 75A
  orderNo 77
  title `Excuse for delay in presentment for acceptance or payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45652&sectionno=75A&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_75_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[75A. Excuse for delay in presentment for acceptance or payment--Delay in presentment ^2[for`
  line `acceptance or payment] is excused if the delay is caused by circumstances beyond the control of the`
  line `holder, and not imputable to his default, misconduct or negligence. When the cause of delay ceases to`
  line `operate, presentment must be made within a reasonable time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_75_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1920, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 1921, s. 3, for "for payment".`
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (45653)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 78
  title `When presentment unnecessary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45653&sectionno=76&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `No presentment for payment is necessary, and the instrument`
  line `is dishonoured at the due date for presentment, in any of the following cases:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the maker, drawee or acceptor intentionally prevents the presentment of the instrument,`
  line or,
  line
  line `if the instrument being payable at his place of business, he closes such place on a business day`
  line `during the usual business hours, or,`
  line
  line `if the instrument being payable at some other specified place, neither he nor any person`
  line `authorized to pay it attends at such place during the usual business hours, or,`
  line
  line `if the instrument not being payable at any specified place, he cannot after due search be`
  line found;
  line
  line `(b) as against any party sought to be charged therewith, if he has engaged to pay notwithstanding`
  line non-presentment;
  line
  line `(c) as against any party if, after maturity, with knowledge that the instrument has not been`
  line presented--
  line
  line `he makes a part payment on account of the amount due on the instrument,`
  line
  line `or promises to pay the amount due thereon in whole or in part,`
  line
  line `or otherwise waives his right to take advantage of any default in presentment for payment;`
  line
  line `(d) as against the drawer, if the drawer could not suffer damage from the want of such`
  line presentment.
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (45654)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 79
  title `Liability of banker for negligently dealing with bill presented for payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45654&sectionno=77&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `When a bill of`
  line `exchange, accepted payable at a specified bank, has been duly presented there for payment and`
  line `dishonoured, if the banker so negligently or improperly keeps, deals with or delivers back such bill as to`
  line `cause loss to the holder, he must compensate the holder for such loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (45655)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 80
  title `To whom payment should be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45655&sectionno=78&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 82, clause (c),`
  line `payment of the amount due on a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque must, in order to discharge`
  line `the maker or acceptor, be made to the holder of the instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (45656)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 81
  title `Interest when rate specified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45656&sectionno=79&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `When interest at a specified rate is expressly made payable on a`
  line `promissory note or bill of exchange, interest shall be calculated at the rate specified, on the amount of the principal money due thereon, from the date of the instrument, until tender or realization of such amount,`
  line `or until such date after the institution of a suit to recover such amount as the Court directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (45657)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 82
  title `Interest when no rate specified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45657&sectionno=80&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `When no rate of interest is specified in the instrument,`
  line `interest on the amount due thereon shall, ^1[notwithstanding any agreement relating to interest between any`
  line `parties to the instrument], be calculated at the rate of ^2[eighteen per centum] per annum, from the date at`
  line `which the same ought to have been paid by the party charged, until tender or realization of the amount`
  line `due thereon, or until such date after the institution of a suit to recover such a mount as the Court directs.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- When the party charged is the indorser of an instrument dishonoured by non-payment,`
  line `he is liable to pay interest only from the time that he receives notice of the dishonour.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 30 of 1926, s. 2, for "except in cases provided for by the Code of Civil Procedure, s. 532".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 2, for "six per centum" (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (45658)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 83
  title `Delivery of instrument on payment or indemnity in case of loss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45658&sectionno=81&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Any person liable to`
  line `pay, and called upon by the holder thereof to pay, the amount due on a promissory note, bill of exchange`
  line `or cheque is before payment entitled to have it shown, and is on payment entitled to have it delivered up,`
  line `to him, or if the instrument is lost or cannot be produced, to be indemnified against any further claim`
  line `thereon against him.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Where the cheque is an electronic image of a truncated cheque, even after the payment the`
  line `banker who received the payment shall be entitled to retain the truncated cheque.`
  line
  line `(3) A certificate issued on the foot of the printout of the electronic image of a truncated cheque by the`
  line `banker who paid the instrument, shall be prima facie proof of such payment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 81 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 55 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (45659)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 84
  title `Discharge from liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45659&sectionno=82&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `The maker, acceptor or indorser respectively of a negotiable`
  line `instrument is discharged from liability thereon--`
  line
  line `(a) by cancellation.-- to a holder thereof who cancels such acceptor's or indorser's name with`
  line `intent to discharge him, and to all parties claiming under such holder;`
  line
  line `(b) by release.-- to a holder thereof who otherwise discharges such maker, acceptor or indorser,`
  line `and to all parties deriving title under such holder after notice of such discharge;`
  line
  line `(c) by payment.-- to all parties thereto, if the instrument is payable to bearer, or has been`
  line `indorsed in blank, and such maker, acceptor or indorser makes payment in due course of the amount`
  line `due thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (45660)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 85
  title `Discharge by allowing drawee more than forty-eight hours to accept.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1921, s. 2, for twenty-four.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45660&sectionno=83&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `If the holder of a bill`
  line `of exchange allows the drawee more than ^1[forty-eight] hours, exclusive of public holidays, to consider`
  line `whether he will accept the same, all previous parties not consenting to such allowance are thereby`
  line `discharge from liability to such holder.`
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (45661)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 86
  title `When cheque not duly presented and drawer damaged thereby.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1897, s. 3, for s. 84.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45661&sectionno=84&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `^1[84. When cheque not duly presented and drawer damaged thereby.--(1) Where a cheque is not`
  line `presented for payment within a reasonable time of its issue, and the drawer or person on whose account it`
  line `is drawn had the right, at the time when presentment ought to have been made, as between himself and`
  line `the banker, to have the cheque paid and suffers actual damage through the delay, he is discharged to the`
  line `extent of such damage, that is to say, to the extent to which such drawer or person is a creditor of the`
  line `banker to a large amount than he would have been if such cheque had been paid.`
  line
  line `(2) In determining what is a reasonble time, regard shall be had to the nature of the instrument, the`
  line `usage of trade and of bankers, and the facts of the particular case.`
  line
  line `(3) The holder of the cheque as to which such drawer or person is so discharged shall be a creditor, in`
  line `lieu of such drawer or person, of such banker to the extent of such discharge and entitled to recover the`
  line `amount from him.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A draws a cheque for Rs. 1,000, and, when the cheque ought to be presented, has funds at the bank to meet`
  line `it. The bank fails before the cheque is presented. The drawer is discharged, but the holder can prove against the bank`
  line `for the amount of the cheque.`
  line
  line `(b) A draws a cheque at Umballa on a bank in Calcutta. The bank fails before the cheque could be presented`
  line `in ordinary course. A is not discharged, for he has not suffered actual damage through any delay in presenting the`
  line cheque.]
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (45662)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 87
  title `Cheque payable to order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45662&sectionno=85&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Where a cheque payable to order purports to be endorsed by`
  line `or on behalf of the payee, the drawee is discharged by payment in due course.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Where a cheque is originally expressed to be payable to bearer, the drawee is discharged`
  line `by payment in due course to the bearer thereof, notwithstanding any endorsement whether in full or`
  line `in blank appearing thereon, and notwithstanding that any such endorsement purports to restrict or`
  line `exclude further negotiation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 85 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 17 of 1934, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_a:
  sectionId (45663)
  sectionNo 85A
  orderNo 88
  title `Drafts drawn by one branch of a bank on another payable to order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1930, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45663&sectionno=85A&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_85_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[85A. Drafts drawn by one branch of a bank on another payable to order.--where any draft, that`
  line `is an order to pay money, drawn by one office of a bank upon another office of the same bank for a sum`
  line `of money payable to order on demand, purports to be endorsed by or on behalf of the payee, the bank is`
  line `discharged by payment in due course.]`
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (45664)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 89
  title `Parties not consenting discharged by qualified or limited acceptance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45664&sectionno=86&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `If the holder of a`
  line `bill of exchange acquiesces in a qualified acceptance, or one limited to part of the sum mentioned in`
  line `the bill, or which substitutes a different place or time for payment, or which, where the drawees are`
  line `not partners, is not signed by all the drawees, all previous parties whose consent is not obtained to`
  line `such acceptance are discharged as against the holder and those claiming under him, unless on notice`
  line `given by the holder they assent to such acceptance.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- An acceptance is qualified--`
  line
  line `(a) where it is conditional, declaring the payment to be dependent on the happening of an event`
  line `therein stated;`
  line
  line `(b) where it undertakes the payment of part only of the sum ordered to be paid;`
  line
  line `(c) where no place of payment being specified on the order, it undertakes the payment at a`
  line `specified place, and not otherwise or elsewhere; or where, a place of payment being specified in the`
  line `order, it undertakes the payment at some other place and not otherwise or elsewhere;`
  line
  line `(d) where it undertakes the payment at a time other than that at which under the order it would be`
  line `legally due.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (45665)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 90
  title `Effect of material alteration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45665&sectionno=87&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `Any material alteration of a negotiable instrument renders the`
  line `same void as against anyone who is a party thereto at the time of making such alteration and does not`
  line `consent thereto, unless it was made in order to carry out the common intention of the original parties;`
  line
  line `Alteration by indorsee.-- And any such alteration, if made by an indorsee, discharges his indorser`
  line `from all liability to him in respect of the consideration thereof.`
  line
  line `The provisions of this section are subject to those of sections 20, 49, 86 and 125.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (45666)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 91
  title `Acceptor or indorser bound notwithstanding previous alteration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45666&sectionno=88&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `An acceptor or indorser of`
  line `a negotiable instrument is bound by his acceptance or indorsement notwithstanding any previous`
  line `alteration of the instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (45667)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 92
  title `Payment of instrument on which alteration is not apparent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45667&sectionno=89&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Where a promissory note,`
  line `bill of exchange or cheque has been materially altered but does not appear to have been so altered, or`
  line `where a cheque is presented for payment which does not at the time of presentation appear to be crossed`
  line `or to have had a crossing which has been obliterated, payment thereof by a person or banker liable to pay,`
  line `and paying the same according to the apparent tenor thereof at the time of payment and otherwise in due`
  line `course, shall discharge such person or banker from all liability thereon; and such payment shall not be`
  line `questioned by reason of the instrument having been altered or the cheque crossed.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Where the cheque is an electronic image of a truncated cheque, any difference in apparent tenor`
  line `of such electronic image and the truncated cheque shall be a material alteration and it shall be the duty of`
  line `the bank or the clearing house, as the case may be, to ensure the exactness of the apparent tenor of`
  line `electronic image of the truncated cheque while truncating and transmitting the image.`
  line
  line `(3) Any bank or a clearing house which receives a transmitted electronic image of a truncated cheque,`
  line `shall verify from the party who transmitted the image to it, that the image so transmitted to it and received`
  line `by it, is exactly the same.]`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 89 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 55 of 2002, s. 5 (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by, s. 5, ibid, (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (45668)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 93
  title `Extinguishment of rights of action on bill in acceptor's hands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45668&sectionno=90&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `If a bill of exchange which`
  line `has been negotiated is, at or after maturity, held by the acceptor in his own right, all rights of action`
  line `thereon are extinguished.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (45669)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 94
  title `Dishonour by non-acceptance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45669&sectionno=91&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `A bill of exchange is said to be dishonoured by non-acceptance`
  line `when the drawee, or one of several drawees not being partners, makes default in acceptance upon being`
  line `duly required to accept the bill, or where presentment is excused and the bill is not accepted.`
  line
  line `Where the drawee is incompetent to contract, or the acceptance is qualified the bill may be treated as`
  line dishonoured.
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (45670)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 95
  title `Dishonour by non-payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45670&sectionno=92&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `A promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque is said to be`
  line `dishonoured by non-payment when the maker of the note, acceptor of the bill or drawee of the cheque`
  line `makes default in payment upon being duly required to pay the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (45671)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 96
  title `By and to whom notice should be given.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45671&sectionno=93&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `When a promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque`
  line `is dishonoured by non-acceptance or non-payment, the holder thereof, or some party thereto who remains`
  line `liable thereon, must give notice that the instrument has been so dishonoured to all other parties whom the`
  line `holder seeks to make severally liable thereon, and to some one of several parties whom he seeks to make`
  line `jointly liable thereon.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section renders it necessary to give notice to the maker of the dishonoured promissory`
  line `note or the drawee or acceptor of the dishonoured bill of exchange or cheque.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (45672)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 97
  title `Mode in which notice may be given.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45672&sectionno=94&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `Notice of dishonour may be given to a duly authorized agent`
  line `of the person to whom it is required to be given, or, where he has died, to his legal representative, or, where he`
  line `has been declared an insolvent, to his assignee; may be oral or written; may, if written, be sent by post; and`
  line `may be in any form; but it must inform the party to whom it is given, either in express terms or by reasonable`
  line `intendment, that the instrument has been dishonoured, and in what way, and that he will be held liable thereon;`
  line `and it must be given within a reasonable time after dishonour, at the place of business or (in case such party`
  line `has no place of business) at the residence of the party for whom it is intended.`
  line
  line `If the notice is duly directed and sent by post and miscarries, such miscarriage does not render the`
  line `notice invalid.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (45673)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 98
  title `Party receiving must transmit notice of dishonour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45673&sectionno=95&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `Any party receiving notice of dishonour`
  line `must, in order to render any prior party liable to himself, give notice of dishonour to such party within a`
  line `reasonable time, unless such party otherwise receives due notice as provided by section 93.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (45674)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 99
  title `Agent for presentment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45674&sectionno=96&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `When the instrument is deposited with an agent for presentment, the`
  line `agent is entitled to the same time to give notice to his principal as if he were the holder giving notice of`
  line `dishonour, and the principal is entitled to a further like period to give notice of dishonour.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (45675)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 100
  title `When party to whom notice given is dead.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45675&sectionno=97&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `when the party to whom notice of dishonour is`
  line `dispatched is dead, but the party dispatching the notice is ignorant of his death, the notice is sufficient.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (45676)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 101
  title `When notice of dishonour is unnecessary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45676&sectionno=98&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `No notice of dishonour is necessary--`
  line
  line `(a) when it is dispensed with by the party entitled thereto;`
  line
  line `(b) in order to charge the drawer, when he has countermanded payment;`
  line
  line `(c) when the party charged could not suffer damage for want of notice;`
  line
  line `(d) when the party entitled to notice cannot after due search be found; or the party bound to give`
  line `notice is, for any other reason, unable without any fault of his own to give it;`
  line
  line `(e) to charge the drawers, when the acceptor is also a drawer;`
  line
  line `(f) in the case of a promissory note which is not negotiable;`
  line
  line `(g) when the party entitled to notice, knowing the facts, promises unconditionally to pay the`
  line `amount due on the instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (45677)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 102
  title Noting.
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45677&sectionno=99&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `When a promissory note or bill of exchange has been dishonoured by non-acceptance`
  line `or non-payment, the holder may cause such dishonour to be noted by a notary public upon the instrument,`
  line `or upon a paper attached thereto, or partly upon each.`
  line
  line `Such note must be made within a reasonable time after dishonour, and must specify the date of`
  line `dishonour, the reason, if any, assigned for such dishonour, or, if the instrument has not been expressly`
  line `dishonoured, the reason why the holder treats it as dishonoured, and the notary's charges.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (45678)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 103
  title Protest.
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45678&sectionno=100&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `When a promissory note or bill of exchange has been dishonoured by non-acceptance`
  line `or non-payment, the holder may, within a reasonable time, cause such dishonour to be noted and certified`
  line `by a notary public. Such certificate is called a protest.`
  line
  line `Protest for better security.-- When the acceptor of a bill of exchange has become insolvent, or`
  line `his credit has been publicly impeached, before the maturity of the bill, the holder may, within a`
  line `reasonable time, cause a notary public to demand better security of the acceptor, and on its being`
  line `refused may, within a reasonable time, cause such facts to be noted and certified as aforesaid. Such`
  line `certificate is called a protest for better security`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (45679)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 104
  title `Contents of protest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1885, s. 5.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45679&sectionno=101&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `A protest under section 100 must contain--`
  line
  line `(a) either the instrument itself, or a literal transcript of the instrument and of everything written`
  line `or printed thereupon;`
  line
  line `(b) the name of the person for whom and against whom the instrument has been protested;`
  line
  line `(c) a statement that payment or acceptance, or better security, as the case may be, has been`
  line `demanded of such person by the notary public; the terms of his answer, if any, or a statement that he`
  line `gave no answer or that he could not be found;`
  line
  line `(d) when the note or bill has been dishonoured, the place and time of dishonour, and, when better`
  line `security has been refused, the place and time of refusal;`
  line
  line `(e) the subscription of the notary public making the protest;`
  line
  line `(f) in the event of an acceptance for honour or of a payment for honour, the name of the person by`
  line `whom, of the person for whom, and the manner in which, such acceptance or payment was offered`
  line `and effected.`
  line
  line `^1[A notary public may make the demand mentioned in clause (c) of this section either in person or`
  line `by his clerk or, where authorized by agreement or usage, by registered letter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (45680)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 105
  title `Notice of protest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45680&sectionno=102&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `When a promissory note or bill of exchange is required by law to be`
  line `protested, notice of such protest must be given instead of notice of dishonour, in the same manner and`
  line `subject to the same conditions; but the notice may be given by the notary public who makes the protest.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (45681)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 106
  title `Protest for non-payment after dishonour by non-acceptance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45681&sectionno=103&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `All bills of exchange drawn`
  line `payable at some other place than the place mentioned as the residence of the drawee, and which are`
  line `dishonoured by non-acceptance, may, without further presentment to the drawee, be protested for nonpayment, in the place specified for payment, unless paid before or at maturity.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (45682)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 107
  title `Protest of foreign bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45682&sectionno=104&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `Foreign bills of exchange must be protested for dishonour when such`
  line `protest is required by the law of the place where they are drawn.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104_a:
  sectionId (45683)
  sectionNo 104A
  orderNo 108
  title `When noting equivalent to protest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45683&sectionno=104A&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_104_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[104A. When noting equivalent to protest.--For the purposes of this Act, where a bill of note is`
  line `required to be protested within a specified time or before some further proceeding is taken it is sufficient`
  line `that the bill has been noted for protest before the expiration of the specified time or the taking of the`
  line `proceeding; and, the formal protest may be extended at any time thereafter as of the date of the noting.]`
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (45684)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 109
  title `Reasonable time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45684&sectionno=105&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `In determining what is a reasonable time for presentment for acceptance or`
  line `payment, for giving notice of dishonour and for noting, regard shall be had to the nature of the instrument`
  line `and the usual course of dealing with respect to similar instruments; and, in calculating such time, public`
  line `holidays shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (45685)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 110
  title `Reasonable time of giving notice of dishonour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45685&sectionno=106&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `If the holder and the party to whom notice of`
  line `dishonour is given carry on business or live (as the case may be) in different places, such notice is given`
  line `within a reasonable time if it is dispatched by the next post or on the day next after the day of dishonour.`
  line
  line `If the said parties carry on business or live in the same place, such notice is given within a reasonable`
  line `time if it is dispatched in time to reach its destination on the day next after the day of dishonour.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (45686)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 111
  title `Reasonable time for transmitting such notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45686&sectionno=107&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `A party receiving notice of dishonour, who`
  line `seeks to enforce his right against a prior party, transmits the notice within a reasonable time if he`
  line `transmits it within the same time after its receipt as he would have had to give notice if he had been the`
  line holder.
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (45687)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 112
  title `Acceptance for honour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes `1. The second sentence rep. by s. 7, ibid,.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45687&sectionno=108&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `When a bill of exchange has been noted or protested for nonacceptance or for better security, any person not being a party already liable thereon may, with the`
  line `consent of the holder, by writing on the bill, accept the same for the honour of any party thereto. ^1***`
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (45688)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 113
  title `How acceptance for honour must be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45688&sectionno=109&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `A person desiring to accept for honour must,`
  line `^1[by writing on the bill under his hand, declare that he accepts under protest the protested bill for the`
  line `honour of the drawer or of a particular indorser whom he names, or generally for honour. ^2`
  line ***
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for in the presence of a notary public, subscribe the bill with his own hand, and.`
  line
  line `2. The words and such declaration must be recorded by the notary in his register rep. by s. 8, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (45689)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 114
  title `Acceptance not specifying for whose honour it is made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45689&sectionno=110&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `Where the acceptance does not`
  line `express for whose honour it is made it shall be deemed to be made for the honour of the drawer.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (45690)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 115
  title `Liability of acceptor for honour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45690&sectionno=111&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `An acceptor for honour binds himself to all parties`
  line `subsequent to the party for whose honour he accepts to pay the amount of the bill if the drawee do not;`
  line `and such party and all prior parties are liable in their respective capacities to compensate the acceptor for`
  line `honour for all loss or damage sustained by him in consequence of such acceptance.`
  line
  line `But an acceptor for honour is not liable to the holder of the bill unless it is presented, or (in case the`
  line `address given by such acceptor on the bill is a place other than the place where the bill is made payable)`
  line `forwarded for presentment, not later than the day next after the day of its maturity.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (45691)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 116
  title `When acceptor for honour may be charged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45691&sectionno=112&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `An acceptor for honour cannot be charged`
  line `unless the bill has at its maturity been presented to the drawee for payment, and has been dishonoured by`
  line `him, and noted or protested for such dishonour.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (45692)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 117
  title `Payment for honour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1885, s. 9.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45692&sectionno=113&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `When a bill of exchange has been noted or protested for non-payment,`
  line `any person may pay the same for the honour of any party liable to pay the same: provided that the person`
  line `so paying ^1[or his agent in that behalf] has previously declared before a notary public the party for whose`
  line `honour he pays, and that such declaration has been recorded by such notary public.`
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (45693)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 118
  title `Right of payer for honour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45693&sectionno=114&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `Any person so paying is entitled to all the rights in respect of the`
  line `bill, of the holder at the time of such payment, and may recover from the party for whose honour he pays`
  line `all sums so paid, with interest thereon and with all expenses properly incurred in making such payment.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (45694)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 119
  title `Drawee in case of need.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45694&sectionno=115&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `Where a drawee in case of need is named in a bill of exchange, or in`
  line `any indorsement thereon, the bill is not dishonoured until it has been dishonoured by such drawee.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (45695)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 120
  title `Acceptance and payment without protest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45695&sectionno=116&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `A drawee in case of need may accept and pay the`
  line `bill of exchange without previous protest.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (45696)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 121
  title `Rules as to compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45696&sectionno=117&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `The compensation payable in case of dishonour of a promissory`
  line `note, bill of exchange or cheque, by any party liable to the holder or any indorsee, shall ^1*** be`
  line `determined by the following rules:--`
  line
  line `(a) the holder is entitled to the amount due upon the instrument together with the expenses`
  line `properly incurred in presenting, noting and protesting it;`
  line
  line `(b) when the person charged resides at a place different from that at which the instrument was`
  line `payable, the holder is entitled to receive such sum at the current rate of exchange between the two`
  line places;
  line
  line `(c) an indorser who, being liable, has paid the amount due on the same is entitled to the amount`
  line `so paid with interest at ^2[eighteen per centum] per annum from the date of payment until tender or`
  line `realization thereof, together with all expenses caused by the dishonour and payment;`
  line
  line `(d) when the person charged and such indorser reside at different places, the indorser is entitled to`
  line `receive such sum at the current rate of exchange between the two places;`
  line
  line `(e) the party entitled to compensation may draw a bill upon the party liable to compensate him,`
  line `payable at sight or on demand, for the amount due to him, together with all expenses properly`
  line `incurred by him. Such bill must be accompanied by the instrument dishonoured and the protest`
  line `thereof (if any). If such bill is dishonoured, the party dishonouring the same is liable to make`
  line `compensation thereof in the same manner as in the case of the original bill.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The brackets, words and figures "(except in cases provided for by the Code of Civil Procedure, s. 532,)" omitted by Act 30 of 1926 , s. . 3.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988 , s. 3 , for "six per centum" (w.e.f . 30 - 12 - 1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (45697)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 122
  title `Presumptions as to negotiable instruments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45697&sectionno=118&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `Until the contrary is proved, the following`
  line `presumptions shall be made:--`
  line
  line `(a) of consideration:-- that every negotiable instrument was made or drawn for consideration,`
  line `and that every such instrument, when it has been accepted, indorsed, negotiated or transferred, was`
  line `accepted, indorsed, negotiated or transferred for consideration;`
  line
  line `(b) as to date:-- that every negotiable instrument bearing a date was made or drawn on such date;`
  line
  line `(c) as to time of acceptance: that every accepted bill of exchange was accepted within a`
  line `reasonable time after its date and before its maturity;`
  line
  line `(d) as to time of transfer:-- that every transfer of a negotiable instrument was made before its`
  line naturity;
  line
  line `(e) as to order of indorsements:-- that the indorsements appearing upon a negotiable instrument`
  line `were made in the order in which they appear thereon;`
  line
  line `(f) as to stamp:-- that a lost promissory note, bill of exchange or cheque was duly stamped;`
  line
  line `(g) that holder is a holder in due course:-- that the holder of a negotiable instrument is a`
  line `holder in due course : provided that, where the instrutment has been obtained from its lawful owner,`
  line `or from any person in lawful custody thereof, by means of an offence or fraud, or has been obtained`
  line `from the maker or acceptor thereof by means of an offence or fraud, or for unlawful consideration, the`
  line `burden of proving that the holder is a holder in due course lies upon him.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (45698)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 123
  title `Presumption on proof of protest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45698&sectionno=119&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `In a suit upon an instrument which has been`
  line `dishonoured, the Court shall, on proof of the protest, presume the fact of dishonour, unless and until`
  line `such fact is disproved.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (45699)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 124
  title `Estoppel against denying original validity of instrument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45699&sectionno=120&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `No maker of a promissory note,`
  line `and no drawer of a bill of exchange or cheque, and no acceptor of a bill of exchange for the honour of the`
  line `drawer shall, in a suit thereon by a holder in due course, be permitted to deny the validity of the`
  line `instrument as originally made or drawn.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (45700)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 125
  title `Estoppel against denying capacity of payee to indorse.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 1919, s. 5, for payable to, or to the orderof, a specified person.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45700&sectionno=121&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `No maker of a promissory note and`
  line `no acceptor of a bill of exchange ^1[payable to order] shall, in a suit thereon by a holder in due course, be`
  line `permitted to deny the payee's capacity, at the date of the note or bill, to indorse the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (45701)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 126
  title `Estoppel against denying signature or capacity of prior party.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45701&sectionno=122&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `No indorser of a negotiable`
  line `instrument shall, in a suit thereon by a subsequent holder, be permitted to deny the signature or capacity`
  line `to contract of any prior party to the instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (45702)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 127
  title `Cheque crossed generally.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45702&sectionno=123&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `Where a cheque bears across its face an addition of the words`
  line `"and company" or any abbreviation thereof, between two parallel transverse lines, or of two parallel`
  line `transverse lines simply, either with or without the words "not negotiable," that addition shall be deemed a`
  line `crossing, and the cheque shall be deemed to be crossed generally`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (45703)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 128
  title `Cheque crossed specially.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45703&sectionno=124&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `Where a cheque bears across its face an addition of the name of a`
  line `banker, either with or without the words "not negotiable," that addition shall be deemed a crossing and`
  line `the cheque shall be deemed to be crossed specially, and to be crossed to that banker.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (45704)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 129
  title `Crossing after issue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45704&sectionno=125&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `Where a cheque is uncrossed, the holder may cross it generally or`
  line specially.
  line
  line `Where a cheque is crossed generally, the holder may cross it specially.`
  line
  line `Where a cheque is crossed generally, or specially, the holder may add the words "not negotiable".`
  line
  line `Where a cheque is crossed specially, the banker to whom it is crossed may again cross it specially to`
  line `another banker, his agent, for collection.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (45705)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 130
  title `Payment of cheque crossed generally.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45705&sectionno=126&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `Where a cheque is crossed generally, the banker on`
  line `whom it is drawn shall not pay it otherwise than to a banker.`
  line
  line `Payment of cheque crossed specially.--Where a cheque is crossed specially, the banker on whom it`
  line `is drawn shall not pay it otherwise than to the banker to whom it is crossed, or his agent for collection.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (45706)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 131
  title `Payment of cheque crossed specially more than once.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45706&sectionno=127&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `Where a cheque is crossed specially`
  line `to more than one banker, except when crossed to an agent for the purpose of collection, the banker on`
  line `whom it is drawn shall refuse payment thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (45707)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 132
  title `Payment in due course of crossed cheque.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45707&sectionno=128&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `Where the banker on whom a crossed cheque is`
  line `drawn has paid the same in due course, the banker paying the cheque, and (in case such cheque has come`
  line `to the hands of the payee) the drawer thereof, shall respectively be entitled to the same rights, and be placed in the same position in all respects, as they would respectively be entitled to and placed in if the`
  line `amount of the cheque had been paid to and received by the true owner thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (45708)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 133
  title `Payment of crossed cheque out of due course.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45708&sectionno=129&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `Any banker paying a cheque crossed`
  line `generally otherwise than to a banker, or a cheque crossed specially otherwise than to the banker to whom`
  line `the same is crossed, or his agent for collection, being a banker, shall be liable to the true owner of the`
  line `cheque for any loss he may sustain owing to the cheque having been so paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (45709)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 134
  title `Cheque bearing ''not negotiable''.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45709&sectionno=130&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `A person taking a cheque crossed generally or specially,`
  line `bearing in either case the words "not negotiable," shall not have, and shall not be capable of giving, a`
  line `better title to the cheque than that which the person from whom he took it had.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (45710)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 135
  title `Non-liability of banker receiving payment of cheque.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45710&sectionno=131&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `A banker who has in good faith and`
  line `without negligence received payment for a customer of a cheque crossed generally or specially to himself`
  line `shall not, in case the title to the cheque proves defective, incur any liability to the true owner of the`
  line `cheque by reason only of having received such payment.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation ^2[(I)].-- A banker receives payment of a crossed cheque for a customer within the`
  line `meaning of this section notwithstanding that he credits his customer's account with the amount of the`
  line `cheque before receiving payment thereof.]`
  line
  line `^3[Explanation II.-- It shall be the duty of the banker who receives payment based on an electronic`
  line `image of a truncated cheque held with him, to verify the prima facie genuineness of the cheque to be`
  line `truncated and any fraud, forgery or tampering apparent on the face of the instrument that can be verified`
  line `with due diligence and ordinary care.]`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1922, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Explanation re-numbered as Explanation I thereof by Act 55 of 2002, s. 6 (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 55 of 2002, s. 6 (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_131_a:
  sectionId (45711)
  sectionNo 131A
  orderNo 136
  title `Application of Chapter to drafts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1947, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45711&sectionno=131A&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_131_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[The provisions of this Chapter shall apply to any draft,`
  line `as defined in section 85A, as if the draft were a cheque.]`
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (45712)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 137
  title `Set of bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45712&sectionno=132&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `Bills of exchange may be drawn in parts, each part being numbered and containing`
  line `a provision that it shall continue payable only so long as the others remain unpaid. All the parts together`
  line `make a set; but the whole set constitutes only one bill, and is extinguished when one of the parts, if a`
  line `separate bill, would be extinguished.`
  line `Exception.—When a person accepts or indorses different parts of the bill in favour of different`
  line `persons, he and the subsequent endorsers of each part are liable on such part as if it were a separate bill.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (45713)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 138
  title `Holder of first acquired part entitled to.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45713&sectionno=133&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `As between holders in due course of different parts`
  line `of the same set, he who first acquired title to his part is entitled to the other parts and the money`
  line `represented by the bill.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (45714)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 139
  title `Law governing liability of maker, acceptor or indorser of foreign instrument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch. for the States.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45714&sectionno=134&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `In the absence`
  line `of a contract to the contrary, the liability of the maker or drawer of a foreign promissory note, bill of`
  line `exchange or cheque is regulated in all essential matters by the law of the place where he made the instrument,`
  line `and the respective liabilities of the acceptor and indorser by the law of the place where the instrument is made`
  line payable.
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A bill of exchange was drawn by A in California, where the rate of interest is 25 per cent., and accepted by B, payable in`
  line `Washington, where the rate of interest is 6 per cent. The bill is erdorsed in ^1[India[, and is dishonoured. An action on the bill is`
  line `brought against B in ^1[India]. He is liable to pay interest at the rate of 6 per cent. only; but if A is charged as drawer, A is liable to`
  line `pay interest at the rate of 25 per cent.`
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (45715)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 140
  title `Law of place of payment governs dishonour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the sch. for "the states".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45715&sectionno=135&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `here a promissory note, bill of exchange or`
  line `cheque is made payable in a different place from that in which it is made or indorsed, the law of the place`
  line `where it is made payable determines what constitutes dishonour and what notice of dishonour is`
  line sufficient.
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A bill of exchange drawn and indorsed in ^1[India], but accepted payable in France, is dishonoured. The indorsee causes it to`
  line `be protested for such dishonour, and gives notice thereof in accordance with the law of France, though not in accordance with the`
  line `rules herein contained in respect of bills which are not foreign. The notice is sufficient.`
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (45716)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 141
  title `Instrument made, etc., out of India, but in accordance with the law of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45716&sectionno=136&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `If a`
  line `negotiable instrument is made, drawn, accepted or indorsed ^1[outside India], but in accordance with the`
  line `^2[law of India], the circumstances that any agreement evidenced by such instrument is invalid according`
  line `to the law of the country wherein it was entered into does not invalidate any subsequent acceptance or`
  line `indorsement made thereon ^3[within India].`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, A.O. 1950 and the Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch. for "out of British India".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "law of British India".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for in "British India".`
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (45717)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 142
  title `Presumption as to foreign law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45717&sectionno=137&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `The law of any foreign country ^1*** regarding promissory`
  line `notes, bills of exchange and cheques shall be presumed to be the same as that of ^2`
  line `[India], unless and until`
  line `the contrary is proved.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words or the State of Jammu and Kashmir omitted by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Sch.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, A.O. 1950 and the Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch. for British India.`
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (45718)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 143
  title `Dishonour of cheque for insufficiency, etc., of funds in the account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45718&sectionno=138&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `^1[Where any cheque`
  line `drawn by a person on an account maintained by him with a banker for payment of any amount of money`
  line `to another person from out of that account for the discharge, in whole or in part, of any debt or other`
  line `liability, is returned by the bank unpaid, either because of the amount of money standing to the credit of`
  line `that account is insufficient to honour the cheque or that it exceeds the amount arranged to be paid from`
  line `that account by an agreement made with that bank, such person shall be deemed to have committed an`
  line `offence and shall, without prejudice to any other provision of this Act, be punished with imprisonment for`
  line `^2[a term which may be extended to two years], or with fine which may extend to twice the amount of the`
  line `cheque, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the cheque has been presented to the bank within a period of six months from the date on`
  line `which it is drawn or within the period of its validity, whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(b) the payee or the holder in due course of the cheque, as the case may be, makes a demand for`
  line `the payment of the said amount of money by giving a notice; in writing, to the drawer of the cheque,`
  line `^3[within thirty days] of the receipt of information by him from the bank regarding the return of the`
  line `cheque as unpaid; and`
  line
  line `(c) the drawer of such cheque fails to make the payment of the said amount of money to the payee`
  line `or, as the case may be, to the holder in due course of the cheque, within fifteen days of the receipt of`
  line `the said notice.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, debt of other liability means a legally enforceable debt`
  line `or other liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 66 of 1988, s, 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 55 of 2002, s.7, for certain words (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for within fifteen days (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (45719)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 144
  title `Presumption in favour of holder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45719&sectionno=139&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `It shall be presumed, unless the contrary is proved, that the`
  line `holder of a cheque received the cheque of the nature referred to in section 138 for the discharge, in whole`
  line `or in part, of any debt or other liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (45720)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 145
  title `Defence which may not be allowed in any prosecution under section 138.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45720&sectionno=140&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `It shall not be a`
  line `defence in a prosecution for an offence under section 138 that the drawer had no reason to believe when`
  line `he issued the cheque that the cheque may be dishonoured on presentment for the reasons stated in that`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (45721)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 146
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45721&sectionno=141&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under section 138 is a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any person liable to punishment if he`
  line `proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge, or that he had exercised all due diligence`
  line `to prevent the commission of such offence:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that where a person is nominated as a Director of a company by virtue of his`
  line `holding any office or employment in the Central Government or State Government or a financial`
  line `corporation owned or controlled by the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be,`
  line `he shall not be liable for prosecution under this Chapter.]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, --`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (45722)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 147
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45722&sectionno=142&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),`
  line
  line `(a) no court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under section 138 except upon a`
  line `complaint, in writing, made by the payee or, as the case may be, the holder in due course of the`
  line cheque;
  line
  line `(b) such complaint is made within one month of the date on which the cause of action arises`
  line `under clause (c) of the proviso to section 138:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the cognizance of a complaint may be taken by the Court after the prescribed period,`
  line `if the complainant satisfies the Court that he had sufficient cause for not making a complaint within such`
  line period;]
  line
  line `(c) no court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class`
  line `shall try any offence punishable under section 138.].`
  line
  line `^3[(2) The offence under section 138 shall be inquired into and tried only by a court within whose local jurisdiction,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the cheque is delivered for collection through an account, the branch of the bank where the`
  line `payee or holder in due course, as the case may be, maintains the account, is situated; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the cheque is presented for payment by the payee or holder in due course, otherwise through`
  line `an account, the branch of the drawee bank where the drawer maintains the account, is situated.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of clause (a), where a cheque is delivered for collection at any`
  line `branch of the bank of the payee or holder in due course, then, the cheque shall be deemed to have been`
  line `delivered to the branch of the bank in which the payee or holder in due course, as the case may be,`
  line `maintains the account.]`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 142 numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 26 of 2015, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-6-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 55 of 2002, s. 9 (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. Act 26 of 2015, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-6-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_142_a:
  sectionId (45723)
  sectionNo 142A
  orderNo 148
  title `Validation for transfer of pending cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by, s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f.15-6-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45723&sectionno=142A&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_142_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[142A. Validation for transfer of pending cases.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any judgment, decree, order or direction of any court,`
  line `all cases transferred to the court having jurisdiction under sub-section (2) of section 142, as amended by`
  line `the Negotiable Instruments (Amendment) Ordinance, 2015 (Ord. 6 of 2015), shall be deemed to have`
  line `been transferred under this Act, as if that sub-section had been in force at all material times.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) of section 142 or sub-section (1), where the`
  line `payee or the holder in due course, as the case may be, has filed a complaint against the drawer of a cheque`
  line `in the court having jurisdiction under sub-section (2) of section 142 or the case has been transferred to`
  line `that court under sub-section (1) and such complaint is pending in that court, all subsequent complaints`
  line `arising out of section 138 against the same drawer shall be filed before the same court irrespective of whether those cheques were delivered for collection or presented for payment within the territorial`
  line `jurisdiction of that court.`
  line
  line `(3) If, on the date of the commencement of the Negotiable Instruments (Amendment) Act, 2015 (26`
  line `of 2015), more than one prosecution filed by the same payee or holder in due course, as the case may be,`
  line `against the same drawer of cheques is pending before different courts, upon the said fact having been`
  line `brought to the notice of the court, such court shall transfer the case to the court having jurisdiction under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 142, as amended by the Negotiable Instruments (Amendment) Ordinance, 2015`
  line `(Ord. 6 of 2015), before which the first case was filed and is pending, as if that sub-section had been in`
  line `force at all material times.]`
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (45724)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 149
  title `Power of Court to try cases summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 2002, s. 10 (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45724&sectionno=143&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `^1[143. Power of Court to try cases summarily.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) all offences under this Chapter shall be tried by a Judicial`
  line `Magistrate of the first class or by a Metropolitan Magistrate and the provisions of sections 262 to 265`
  line `(both inclusive) of the said Code shall, as far as may be, apply to such trials:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any conviction in a summary trial under this section, it shall be lawful for`
  line `the Magistrate to pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding one year and an amount of`
  line `fine exceeding five thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when at the commencement of, or in the course of, a summary trial under this`
  line `section, it appears to the Magistrate that the nature of the case is such that a sentence of imprisonment for`
  line `a term exceeding one year may have to be passed or that it is, for any other reason, undesirable to try the`
  line `case summarily, the Magistrate shall after hearing the parties, record an order to that effect and`
  line `thereafter recall any witness who may have been examined and proceed to hear or rehear the case in the`
  line `manner provided by the said Code.`
  line
  line `(2) The trial of a case under this section shall, so far as practicable, consistently with the interests of`
  line `justice, be continued from day to day until its conclusion, unless the Court finds the adjournment of the`
  line `trial beyond the following day to be necessary for reasons to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(3) Every trial under this section shall be conducted as expeditiously as possible and an endeavour`
  line `shall be made to conclude the trial within six months from the date of filing of the complaint.]`
obj_root_law_sections_143_a:
  sectionId (49430)
  sectionNo 143A
  orderNo 150
  title `Power to direct interim compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2018, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-9-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=49430&sectionno=143A&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_143_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[143A. Power to direct interim compensation.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the Court trying an offence under section 138 may order`
  line `the drawer of the cheque to pay interim compensation to the complainant--`
  line
  line `(a) in a summary trial or a summons case, where he pleads not guilty to the accusation made in`
  line `the complaint; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, upon framing of charge.`
  line
  line `(2) The interim compensation under sub-section (1) shall not exceed twenty per cent. of the amount`
  line `of the cheque.`
  line
  line `(3) The interim compensation shall be paid within sixty days from the date of the order under`
  line `sub-section (1), or within such further period not exceeding thirty days as may be directed by the Court on`
  line `sufficient cause being shown by the drawer of the cheque..`
  line
  line `(4) If the drawer of the cheque is acquitted, the Court shall direct the complainant to repay to the`
  line `drawer the amount of interim compensation, with interest at the bank rate as published by the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India, prevalent at the beginning of the relevant financial year, within sixty days from the date of`
  line `the order, or within such further period not exceeding thirty days as may be directed by the Court on`
  line `sufficient cause being shown by the complainant..`
  line
  line `(5) The interim compensation payable under this section may be recovered as if it were a fine under`
  line `section 421 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)..`
  line
  line `(6) The amount of fine imposed under section 138 or the amount of compensation awarded under`
  line `section 357 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall be reduced by the amount paid or`
  line `recovered as interim compensation under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (45725)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 151
  title `Mode of service of summons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45725&sectionno=144&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and for the purposes of this Chapter, a Magistrate issuing a`
  line `summons to an accused or a witness may direct a copy of summons to be served at the place where such`
  line `accused or witness ordinarily resides or carries on business or personally works for gain, by speed post or`
  line `by such courier services as are approved by a Court of Session.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an acknowledgment purporting to be signed by the accused or the witness or an`
  line `endorsement purported to be made by any person authorised by the postal department or the courier services`
  line `that the accused or the witness refused to take delivery of summons has been received, the Court issuing`
  line `the summons may declare that the summons has been duly served.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (45726)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 152
  title `Evidence on affidavit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45726&sectionno=145&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the evidence of the complainant may be given by him on affidavit and may,`
  line `subject to all just exceptions be read in evidence in any enquiry, trial or other proceeding under the said`
  line Code.
  line
  line `(2) The Court may, if it thinks fit, and shall, on the application of the prosecution or the accused,`
  line `summon and examine any person giving evidence on affidavit as to the facts contained therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (45727)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 153
  title `Bank's slip prima facie evidence of certain facts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45727&sectionno=146&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `The Court shall, in respect of every`
  line `proceeding under this Chapter, on production of Bank's slip or memo having thereon the official mark`
  line `denoting that the cheque has been dishonoured, presume the fact of dishonour of such cheque, unless and`
  line `until such fact is disproved.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (45728)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 154
  title `Offences to be compoundable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=45728&sectionno=147&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), every offence punishable under this Act shall be compoundable].`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (49431)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 155
  title `Power of Appellate Court to order payment pending appeal against conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2018, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-9-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701&sectionId=49431&sectionno=148&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00042_00042_1523271998701
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `^1[148. Power of Appellate Court to order payment pending appeal against conviction.--(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), in an appeal by`
  line `the drawer against conviction under section 138, the Appellate Court may order the appellant to deposit`
  line `such sum which shall be a minimum of twenty per cent. of the fine or compensation awarded by the trial`
  line `Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount payable under this sub-section shall be in addition to any interim`
  line `compensation paid by the appellant under section 143A.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount referred to in sub-section (1) shall be deposited within sixty days from the date of the`
  line `order, or within such further period not exceeding thirty days as may be directed by the Court on`
  line `sufficient cause being shown by the appellant.`
  line
  line `(3) The Appellate Court may direct the release of the amount deposited by the appellant to the`
  line `complainant at any time during the pendency of the appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the appellant is acquitted, the Court shall direct the complainant to repay to the`
  line `appellant the amount so released, with interest at the bank rate as published by the Reserve Bank of India,`
  line `prevalent at the beginning of the relevant financial year, within sixty days from the date of the order, or`
  line `within such further period not exceeding thirty days as may be directed by the Court on sufficient cause`
  line `being shown by the complainant.]`
